Title: Out of the Frying Pan
Description: Return the set of pots and pans to Cook Swampy in the Cutlass Keys Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Normally I'd tell you to try the Cutlass Quiche.

But can you believe it, there are some around here who don't like my cooking! My cooking!

Normally I would shrug this off, but not this time.
InProgressResponse:
Have you recovered my pots and pans yet?

I once hit Mister Broadbin with that frying pan, back when he was a young deckhand.

I wonder if he still remembers that. Probably not, from the concussion.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Ah, let’s see… that’s them! No better pans in all Aeternum!

Thank you! I'll have to cook up something special!

Maybe I'll make one of Shillie's favorites.

Title: Recipe for Disaster
Description: Recover Swampy's missing recipes from the Salty Snail Fishery and his cookbook from Misanthrope Broadbin at Pond Scum Fort. Talk to Cook Swampy in the Cutlass Keys Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not yet, though funny you should ask. Having my skillet back got me thinking about something else I’d love to get my hands on.\n\nWhen my old crew turned against me, I had to flee with some haste.
InProgressResponse:
It seems Master Broadbin does remember I hit him with my frying pan.

He's turned our old crew against me!

Please get my cookbook, and recipes, back from those ungrateful wretches.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, you've got my cookbook!\n\nI'll be able to enjoy all my old favorites, like Sea Dog Brew, Bitter Squall, and the infamous Stormsurge Surprise.

Title: In Search of Plunder
Description: Explore the Spiti Ruins to collect artifacts. Search chests to collect William's notes. Talk to Quartermaster Duffy in the Cutlass Keys Settlement when your task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Oh, we do, but it's high time we collected more.

Speaking of collecting, you may be familiar with William Heron.

He came through here and spent time at the Spiti Ruins, though he left disappointed with his finds.
InProgressResponse: All that plunder isn't going to go fall into our laps without some effort!\n\nExplore the ruins and bring back what artifacts you find.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Excellent work! It does my heart good to see such treasures.

Take this ring as a token of our thanks.

You're well on your way to becoming a true pirate!

Title: Relics of the Tower
Description: Loot orbs from statues inside Malocchio Spire. Then Investigate what is at the top of the spire. Talk to Quartermaster Duffy in the Cutlass Keys Settlement when your task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
We could always use more items to sell.

We'll ship that last batch of artifacts you collected to buyers in another settlement.

And Mr. Heron's notes have come in handy.
InProgressResponse: It's not as fun as taking on another ship at sea, but raiding ruins is still quite lucrative.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Magnificent! What unusual artifacts.\n\nI have even heard there may be some in Reekwater who would be interested in purchasing them!

Title: Pirate Island
Description: Raid Pirate Island and recover the papers from the Pirate Figurehead between the Festering Fishery and Clearmon's Doubt. Talk to Quartermaster Duffy in the Cutlass Keys Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We had an arrangement, pirate to pirate, with my old crew.\n\nThose Wormsworn Pirates would leave us alone and attack other places for their supplies.
InProgressResponse: We need to show those pirates what happens when they break their word.\n\nMake them think twice before they raid our supplies again.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Excellent work!

You've recovered everything from inside the figurehead of Sordamor's Honor.

I'm glad you were able to find the hidden compartment.

Title: Explosive Prospecting
Description: Investigate the source of the tremors in the Highpass Mining Camp and diffuse the situation. Talk to Captain Lucian in the Cutlass Key Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Tremors have been originating from a Corrupted mining camp in Ancients Pass.\n\nWe fear it's more than just natural mine disturbances as it has been getting steadily worse.
InProgressResponse: What we don't need is a landslide ruining our fine settlement.\n\nInvestigate the Corrupted mining camp and put a stop to their plans.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Thank you for silencing the hillside, now we can sleep at night.\n\nWe'll have to keep a closer eye on those Corrupted Miners.

Title: Stolen Plans
Description: Recover the stolen building plans and the building supplies from the Corrupted at Rusty Spoon Camp. Talk to Captain Lucian in the Cutlass Keys Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Yes, and it reminds me...

Centuries ago, during construction of the original Cutlass Keys Fort, a wave of Corrupted invaded, forcing us to abandon the site.

We moved the fort to a new location, but it lacks something the old fort had.
InProgressResponse:
Stolen plans, mining explosions...

I worry about what the Corrupted will be up to next.

Those plans will help protect us the next time they strike.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These plans are a thing of beauty.\n\nThe original architect was a master builder, too bad the Corrupted got them.

Title: Lightning in a Bottle
Description: Find elemental materials from spirits and bring them back to Carpenter Fei in the Cutlass Keys Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It seems that way. Bolder, smarter, and using new tactics.\n\nThat's why Captain Lucian has asked me to put some of my skills to the test and find a way to hold them back.
InProgressResponse: We have to find a better way to fight back against the Corrupted.\n\nPerhaps the bottled lightning is the edge we need.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Thank you for bringing these samples back.\n\nNow to unlock their potential, with any luck, they will be effective against the Corrupted!

Title: Lightning Unleashed
Description: Place the Lightning Jars in locations around Fort Ramos. Talk to Carpenter Fei in the Cutlass Keys Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I think I've created a way to slow the spread of Corruption.\n\nThis is the first time I've done something like this, so I'd feel better if we tested it in the field.
InProgressResponse: Those jars aren't going to test themselves.\n\nThey need to be around a high concentration of Corruption.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
They are all in place? Excellent work.

That should slow them down.

I only regret I wasn't there to see them in action.

Title: Toss of a Coin
Description: Travel to Fishbone Village to discover if the rumors about the Touched Coin are true. Talk to Coxwain Bryce in the Cutlass Keys Settlement when your task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Do you know about the Touched Coin? It's supposed to make the bearer incredibly lucky.\n\nPerhaps even lucky enough to find a way off this accursed isle.
InProgressResponse: Don't you want to know if the rumors are true?\n\nI know I'm interested in knowing where the coin is.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So the rumors are true!\n\nNow I know where the coin is, no thanks to Trost. He's convinced the Touched Coin is unlucky.

Title: Heads or Tails (Elite)
Description: Defeat Boatswain Benjamin to collect the Touched Coin. Chose to return the coin to Sailing Master Trost or Coxwain Bryce in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Well, bad luck follows the Touched Coin like seagulls follow a ship, I can't help thinking it attracted Benjamin.\n\nYou know, Rosina and Benjamin used to crew on the same ship.
InProgressResponse: I once owned the Touched Coin, and I regretted every minute of it.\n\nEven after leaving it behind, it still causes problems for me. I need to destroy it to break the cycle.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @1001_0101_heads_tails_complete_available_response

Title: Heads for the Sailing Master
Description: Both Sailing Master Trost and Coxwain Bryce in Cutlass Keys want the Touched Coin.\n\nChoose wisely.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: [BLANK]
InProgressResponse: I need to destroy that coin.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Splendid, you've recovered the coin!\n\nOnce you give it to me, I'm going to make sure its luck never effects anyone ever again.

Title: Tails for the Coxwain
Description: Both Coxwain Bryce and Sailing Master Trost in Cutlass Keys want the Touched Coin.\n\nChoose wisely.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: [BLANK]
InProgressResponse: That coin belonds to me!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Color me impressed, you have the Touched Coin!\n\nQuick, give it to me before Trost can interfere!

Title: Animal Instincts
Description: Gather samples from wildcats and alligators and bring them to Tosch in Cutlass Keys so he can study how to tame them.
PlayerPrompt: "How do you propose to do that?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have a way with animals. I can feel what they feel, know what they know. I can get into their heads and see the world through their eyes. \n\nBut sometimes I need more. I need parts of the animals to understand them.
InProgressResponse: Nature is beautiful, and can be distracting, but you need to stay focused. \n\nRemember the goal - seek out wildcats and alligators!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These are wonderful! Just what I was looking for. I have a feeling I'm getting closer! \n\nCan you imagine having a tame wildcat helping you hunt? Or an alligator keeping the Lost away from your home?

Title: Animal Instincts
Description: Gather samples from wildcats and alligators and bring them to Tosch in Cutlass Keys so he can study how to tame them.
PlayerPrompt: "How do you propose to do that?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have a way with animals. I can feel what they feel, know what they know. I can get into their heads and see the world through their eyes. \n\nBut sometimes I need more. I need parts of the animals to understand them.
InProgressResponse: Nature is beautiful, and can be distracting, but you need to stay focused. \n\nRemember the goal - seek out wildcats and alligators!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These are wonderful! Just what I was looking for. I have a feeling I'm getting closer! \n\nCan you imagine having a tame wildcat helping you hunt? Or an alligator keeping the Lost away from your home?

Title: Snaggletooth
Description: Collect a tooth from a fierce lion and bring it to Tosch in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: A LION! Not just any lion either, but the legendary “Snaggletooth” who lives across the marsh.
InProgressResponse: To catch a lion you need to emulate it - be courageous and boldly go forth to seek it out at Snaggletooth Burrow!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah! So this is the snaggletooth of that famed lion! Wonderful work! \n\nNow, while you were gone I have made some progress studying the wildcat claws and alligator scales.

Title: Catnipping
Description: Gather whiskers from island pumas and bring them to Tosch in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: This time I need you to seek out the elusive island pumas. \n\nBring me back some of their whiskers. By studying the sensitive whiskers, I hope to gain insights on how to calm the pumas, and perhaps other felines.
InProgressResponse: Now is no time to behave like a cat! You need to get out there and collect some whiskers from the island pumas!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These samples are perfect! I can really feel their calming presence. \n\nWe are making progress, but we still seem to be missing an important element.

Title: Taming the Lionhearted
Description: Gather collars and leashes from the Corrupted and bring them to Tosch in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Corrupted! Have you seen how they have dogs which do their bidding up at Fort Ramos? \n\nI must find out how they do it!
InProgressResponse: I'd stay away from the Corrupted too - but those at Fort Ramos have the knowledge I seek! \n\nI must have those collars and leashes!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These are of a good strong make and a solid design. I can see how these would help. \n\nBut there is something about them that feels wrong. Something slimy that worms its way into you the longer you hold them.

Title: Perfect Companion
Description: Gather boar bristles and bring them to Tosch in Cutlass Keys so that he may tame the ultimate pet!
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Find the perfect pet! I have a list here of all the traits I'm looking for. Sturdy, beautiful pelt, keeps my feet warm at night, eats anything, delicious when cooked just in case it goes feral and things don't work out…
InProgressResponse: This won't be boar-ing, I promise! Please find some boar bristles so I can be sure I want one as a pet.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Aha, I can sense already that this will be the key! I’ll have to study these materials, but I feel confident!

Title: A Disturbing Silence
Description: Search for Jocelyn at Castaway Colony. Talk to Swamp Walker Nekumanesh in Cutlass Keys when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh sure, there’s the sound of nature all around us. But I long for something more. Like the sound of my wife’s voice. \n\nTraveling through swamps keeps me away from home more often than I would’ve liked. I find I miss her.
InProgressResponse: Chatting with you is filling the silence, but I long to hear my wife's voice again. Seek Jocelyn out at Castaway Colony.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You didn't see Jocelyn? But I was certain she would be among the colony. I remember her voice as if it was yesterday, \n\n“I’m going to Castaway Colony and don’t you try to follow me with your swampwalking ways!”

Title: Tracking by Teeth
Description: Track Jocelyn by finding her teeth in Flatfish Fishery. Talk to Swamp Walker Nekumanesh in Cutlass Keys when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Seems everyone knows someone who lives, or lived, at Flatfish Fishery. I’m certain Jocelyn would have gone there to her family. \n\nEspecially since she talked so much her teeth were starting to fall out!
InProgressResponse: If only I hadn't gone to help map the swamps in Reekwater. \n\nHave you found my wife, or her teeth? Flatfish Fishery is a good place to start looking.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So, this is all you could find? Just these teeth? You didn't find Jocelyn? \n\nAnd where did you find them? All in one place?

Title: Heart of the Marsh
Description: Find Jocelyn and recover a keepsake from her. Talk to Swamp Walker Nekumanesh in Cutlass Keys when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: More like I have a strong suspicion. I don't think she'll want to speak to me, not after our last argument. \n\nYou’ve already done so much, I hate to ask for another favor, but would you talk to Jocelyn for me?
InProgressResponse: Go on, she doesn't bite, at least, not anymore without her teeth. \n\nYou'll find Jocelyn at Flatfish Fishery.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Did you find Jocelyn? You don't look like you have good news. \n\nAnd what’s this? Her diary? It looks thick enough to be a memoir, there must be six hundred pages in here! This is all so much. What happened?

Title: One Who Tolled the Bells
Description: Travel across the Old Fort Bridge and clear out any alligators too close to it. Talk to Watcher Jie Hu when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah, so you haven't heard of me. You must be new around here, and new to Aeternum. \n\nBack in the day, before your grandparents were born, I used to patrol the bridges of Cutlass Keys and rings bells to warn of any trouble.
InProgressResponse: Have you visited the Old Fort Bridge yet? The longer you wait, the more likely alligators might infest the area around it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So, what did you find? Was there any need to ring out the bells? \n\nHas the bridge fallen into disrepair, or worse, become so infested with alligators that no one could use it?

Title: Bridge to Nowhere
Description: Travel across Flatfish Bridge then clear out any scavengers and alligators near it. Talk to Watcher Jie Hu in Cutlass Keys when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It's from Flatfish Fishery over to the Fort. We called it The Flatfish Bridge back when the fishery ran a bustling business. \n\nI've heard the fishery has been overrun by Lost, which isn't a good sign for the bridge.
InProgressResponse: Travel to Flatfish Bridge. Once you're there, cross the bridge and clear out any alligators or scavengers lurking nearby.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So, how was Flatfish Bridge? As bad as I had feared? \n\nHas it disintegrated from disuse leaving nothing but pylons as reminders of where it once stood?

Title: One Bridge too Far
Description: Travel across the Saltshore Bridge then clear out any Wormsworn Pirates near it. Talk to Watcher Jie Hu in Cutlass Keys when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Over by Cayo de la Muerte, that cursed island. More than one fool has lost their way, and themselves, over there. \n\nI would know. I was one of them. And it has brought nothing but regrets.
InProgressResponse: Travel across the Saltshore Bridge and clear out any pirates that have taken it over.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So tell me, what did you find at the bridge? Was it still standing? It hadn't been burned to the ground? \n\nAnd what of the pirates, were they extracting tolls for its use?

Title: Burning Bridges
Description: Travel across Stone Skull Crossing and clear out any Wormsworn Pirates nearby. Talk to Watcher Jie Hu in Cutlass Keys when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: A long time ago, I took a bribe from the Wormsworn Pirates to abandon my post. I was so tired of fighting all the time. \n\nI thought a nice bribe, take a break for a week, then go back on patrol. It didn't work out that way.
InProgressResponse: It's a long way to Stone Skull Crossing, you best get going if you want to take on those Wormsworn Pirates.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Here. You deserve this more than I ever did.

Title: Treasure Island
Description: Follow the treasure map Claire provided to discover great riches! Talk to Claire Fergus in Cutlass Keys when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The treasure! But really, I need help searching the Yafda Steps. The treasure is there, somewhere. \n\nI admit I haven’t been able to find it, but I have a feeling about you. Surely you’ll be able to bring the treasure back!
InProgressResponse: Aren’t you excited! You’re holding a genuine treasure map! Well, half of one. \n\nMy previous treasure hunting partner took the other half, but this half has the “x” that marks the spot! It leads directly to the Yafda Steps!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This is it? It's just a handful of doubloons! Where's the rest of the treasure? \n\nThe notes that came with the map indicated there should be a chest filled with riches beyond our wildest dreams. Not some scraps of silver.

Title: Trail of the Misanthrope
Description: Track down Claire's partner who stole all the treasure! Talk to Claire Fergus in Cutlass Keys when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'm going after him! No, wait, I have a better idea. Would you search for him? \n\nYou were so good tracking down the treasure from the map, if anyone can find him, you can. He couldn’t have taken the treasure on his own.
InProgressResponse: I still can’t believe it. I should have expected Broadbin to turn on me like that. \n\nGo and recover our treasure from him, and his associates!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Now that's more like it! Look at all that gold! And you even recovered the chest to store it all! \n\nYou're the best treasure hunting partner! Way better than Broadbin ever was! I can’t thank you enough!

Title: Mother Ocean
Description: Recover Billiam's Sextant from the wreck of The Storm Petral, located in the Condemned Shallows. Return the sextant to Wistful Billiam in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: She’s beached in the Condemned Shallows. I’ve been meaning to go back and reclaim my sextant from her. \n\nHowever, some of the old crew are a bit too attached to her. They guard her jealously, and won’t let me take what was mine.
InProgressResponse: I long to look at the stars again through my old sextant. If only I hadn't left it behind. \n\nPlease go to the Storm Petral to find it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You did it! That's my old sextant, looking no worse for wear being away from me. \n\nI guess my old crew really did take care of our ship, and all that was on it. Though even they can’t halt the course of time.

Title: Sea Dreams
Description: Recover Billiam's Astrolabe from a chest at the wreck of the ship Nizam's Foresight, located on the southern beach of Haunted Isle. Return the astrolabe to Wistful Billiam in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I was scouting out the ship Nizam's Foresight. I was hoping to find an intact dinghy, so I could sail out and get a better view of the stars. \n\nBut when I got there, all it had were some withered who decided to rob me!
InProgressResponse: That old astrolabe never failed me. With it, and my sextant, why it would almost be like I was back at sea. \n\nPlease bring it back from those thieves!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Now that astrolabe is a sight for sore eyes. Just look at the way it moves smoothly with no sand in it. \n\nThey don't make these like they used to. In fact, I'm not sure anyone on Aeternum really makes them the old way.

Title: High Tide
Description: Recover Billiam's Sea Charts from the wreck of the ship Sirin's Magnificence, located along the southern edge of Cayo De La Muerte. Return the charts to Wistful Billiam in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Well some of my old crew left the Condemned Shallows, joining up with the Wormsworn Pirates. \n\nThey knew I was charting the tides, and mistakenly thought I was trying to find a way off the island! Those poor fools stole my sea charts!
InProgressResponse: There’s just one more thing I’m missing to really make me feel like I’m back at sea, charting safe paths through storms and treacherous shoals. \n\nPlease recover my sea charts from those miserable pirates!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Will you look at that! My old charts are still legible! The sea hasn't ruined them yet - and neither have those wretched withered! \n\n I’ve been longing to write down what I've seen with my sextant and astrolabe.

Title: The Way the Cookie Crumbles
Description: Recover Junia's winning cookie recipe then find the ingredients used to make it. Talk to Chef Decima Opimius in Cutlass Keys when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: He does! It is most unfair. In the past, Swampy didn't always win the cooking competition. \n\nJunia used to win every year. She was known for her superb cookies, thanks to an old family recipe. We'd bake them together.
InProgressResponse: What are you waiting for? Those cookies aren't going to bake themselves!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Just look at those ingredients! I forgot the delicate sweetness of those honey soaked figs! \n\nAh, I can taste victory already!

Title: Admiral Blackpowder's Fall (Expedition)
Description: Enter the Barnacles and Black Powder Expedition. Gather the chronicles of the infamous Admiral Blackpowder, and take him down for Wally Widdershins.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: HAH!  Caught your ear, did I? Same as the Admiral, feeding us golden lies about mysterious treasure on a magic island. \n\nI smelled a rat, but did anyone believe ole Widdershins? Poor sods. Now they're all Lost, and the Admiral…
InProgressResponse: Admiral Blackpowder... the cruelest man in all the seas, and crueler still with that idol. Soon as you've stamped him into the ground, I'm walking the straight and narrow. Had my fill of thieving and curses. Don't you pick up any of the cursed gold either, you hear?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hah! I heard them cannons roaring! You gave ole Blackpowder a taste of his own medicine, eh? No less than the bastard deserved.\n\nAs for me, my piracy days are over. Maybe I'll take up the fishing pole again…

Title: Mysteries of the Deep (Expedition)
Description: Enter the Barnacles and Black Powder Expedition to disrupt the work of a suspected Water Elemental for Rowan Pennbrook.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Can you imagine? A whole region of Aeternum under water. Of course I can't prove it, but...\n\nI did track a Water Elemental to this very lair. Hopefully those pirate fools haven't reached the Elemental's sanctum, though I suspect it is very deep within the caverns.
InProgressResponse: In my heyday, I hunted all kinds of Elementals across Aeternum. Rare beasts, set by the Angry Earth to guard all the island's secrets from human eyes. Ha, just talking it about gets my blood pumping!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You say she was called a 'Nereid?' Fascinating, fascinating!\n\nEven if this Nereid said nothing about an underwater city, she must have come from somewhere, and come here for some purpose. Now to find out what it was…

Title: Cleansing Treasure (Expedition)
Description: Enter the Barnacles and Black Powder Expedition to collect golden trinkets from the crewmembers. Bring them back to Quiggley Quorus to cleanse and sell them.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Once I was a holy man, but no more, no more. Poverty and celibacy? What a terrible bore!\n\nI stole away with holy water, and the magistrate's dear daughter. Now I'm here to cleanse what can be sold!
InProgressResponse: I've nothing but holy water and wits! You'll fight and bring me the baubles and bits!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I've a buyer in mind, but first must pay you in kind. Take your reward, take your coin, and hurry back with more to purloin!
